 python -m pip install -e '.[forecast]'  # TimesFM + Chronos
 ```
 
+
+## Phase 2C fixed-cutoff real-data workflow
+
+The GitHub Actions workflow `phase2c-real-benchmark.yml` executes a predeclared
+research run with no credentials. It attempts multiple independent spot venues,
+public derivatives history and availability-lagged FRED market context, then writes
+immutable source artifacts, a combined snapshot, sealed benchmark output, ablations,
+quality diagnostics and a prospective freeze candidate.
+
+```bash
+python -m pip install -e '.[exchange,ml]'
+python -m hybrid_trader.phase2c \
+  --spec configs/phase2c_sources.yaml \
+  --config configs/phase2c_btc_4h.yaml \
+  --output artifacts/phase2c
+python scripts/verify_phase2c_artifacts.py artifacts/phase2c
+```
+
+The checked-in specification freezes the observation cutoff, source candidates,
+latency assumptions, split sizes, model list, threshold grid and cost multipliers.
+Changing any of them creates a different experiment identity. Failed public sources
+remain in the registry rather than being silently omitted.
+
+The historical workflow deliberately creates an **empty** prospective ledger. A
+human-reviewed freeze must be activated before any future paper decisions are
+recorded. See [`docs/phase-2c-real-benchmark.md`](docs/phase-2c-real-benchmark.md).
+
